    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix M2AP Scheduling Information Response Handler\n\n### Summary\nThe M2AP MBMS Scheduling Information Response handler in the MCE was not properly processing incoming PDU responses from the eNB. This caused message loss and corruption downstream as critical IE information (MCE_MBMS_M2AP_ID, ENB_MBMS_M2AP_ID) was never extracted from the response.\n\nThe root cause was that the entire PDU processing logic was commented out in the handler function, leaving only skeleton code and a direct ITTI message send without any validation or IE extraction.\n\nThis fix implements the proper PDU parsing logic, extracts and validates the mandatory IEs, and ensures the response is correctly forwarded to the MCE application layer.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/M2AP/m2ap_MCE_interface_management.c`: Uncommented and implemented PDU processing logic in MCE_handle_MBMS_SCHEDULING_INFORMATION_RESPONSE\n- `openair2/M2AP/m2ap_MCE_interface_management.c`: Added proper IE extraction loop with switch statement for MCE_MBMS_M2AP_ID and ENB_MBMS_M2AP_ID\n- `openair2/M2AP/m2ap_MCE_interface_management.c`: Fixed ITTI message sending to use correct instance parameter\n- `openair2/M2AP/m2ap_MCE_interface_management.c`: Added proper logging for debugging\n\n"
}